cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.IR, cs.CL 

This paper deals with large scale video labelling using deep neural networks (DNNs), which is a problem commonly studied in the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) communities. The paper also discusses methods for promoting and measuring DNN diversity, which is a topic relevant to multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR) research. Finally, the paper presents a solution to the video understanding problem, which involves natural language processing (cs.CL) techniques for generating video labels.
